<h1>Cody Burleson</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://codyburleson.com/now/">codyburleson.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Forth Worth
TX
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Co-founder and Software Architect at Base22
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I hammer endlessly on the same spot in the universe, trying to make it dent - trying to make software that makes a real difference.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I believe the most meaningful thing I can do with my experience and talents is create a killer platform for Linked Data and the Semantic Web. I believe that my team can be the one that cracks the nut wide open and helps people see that the Web is still a new frontier; a Web of Linked Data will change the world even more than a Web of linked documents.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Death is imminent. Life is awesome. Make it count.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
You Are Not a Gadget by Jaron Lanier
</p>

